    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7567,
      "reputation" : 10522,
      "user_id" : 13189,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/tKLRf.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "eckes",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13189/eckes"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 24,
    "last_activity_date" : 1432045982,
    "last_edit_date" : 1432045982,
    "creation_date" : 1417648619,
    "answer_id" : 27283480,
    "question_id" : 3101128,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want to make this part of your POM for a repeatable build, you can use the fork-variant of a few of the plugins (especially <a href=\"http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-compiler-plugin/compile-mojo.html\">compiler:compile</a> and <a href=\"http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/test-mojo.html\">surefire:test</a>):</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;plugin&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;3.2&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;configuration&gt;\n      &lt;fork&gt;true&lt;/fork&gt;\n      &lt;meminitial&gt;128m&lt;/meminitial&gt;\n      &lt;maxmem&gt;1024m&lt;/maxmem&gt;\n      &lt;compilerArgs&gt;\n        &lt;arg&gt;-XX:MaxPermSize=256m&lt;/arg&gt;\n      &lt;/compilerArgs&gt;\n    &lt;/configuration&gt;\n  &lt;/plugin&gt;\n\n&lt;plugin&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;2.18&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;configuration&gt;\n        &lt;forkCount&gt;1&lt;/forkCount&gt;\n        &lt;argLine&gt;-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m&lt;/argLine&gt;\n    &lt;/configuration&gt;\n&lt;/plugin&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3723682,
      "reputation" : 697,
      "user_id" : 3098044,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5512e3037e9e511c4ae3304102b6ad73?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "mkumar0304",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3098044/mkumar0304"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1485778088,
    "last_edit_date" : 1485778088,
    "creation_date" : 1484217933,
    "answer_id" : 41611109,
    "question_id" : 3101128,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have found a solution of git bash command when you try to build war using git mvn clean install for\n    “java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space” in Maven build error come</p>\n\n<pre><code>use below command first \n\n$ export MAVEN_OPTS=\"-Xmx512m -Xss32m\"\n\nthen use your mvn command to clean install /build war file\n\n$ mvn clean install\n\nNOTE: you don't need -XX:MaxPermSize argument in MAVEN_OPTS when your are using jdk1.8\nJava HotSpot(TM) Client VM warning: ignoring option MaxPermSize=XXXm; support was removed in 8.0\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3732221,
      "reputation" : 566,
      "user_id" : 4361933,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/PoLhN.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "&#214;MER TAŞCI",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4361933/%c3%96mer-ta%c5%9eci"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1489066858,
    "creation_date" : 1489066858,
    "answer_id" : 42696923,
    "question_id" : 3101128,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>When I encountered this exception, I solved this by using Run Configurations... panel as picture shows below.Especially, at JRE tab, the VM Arguments are the critical <br/> ( <strong>\"-Xmx1024m -Xms512m -XX:MaxPermSize=1024m -XX:PermSize=512m\"</strong> ).</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/gu6p2.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/gu6p2.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5587581,
      "reputation" : 144,
      "user_id" : 4427744,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-NWQv5-HFeAI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAHk/KOla4ALS11k/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Ranjit",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4427744/ranjit"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1491999139,
    "last_edit_date" : 1491999139,
    "creation_date" : 1491998735,
    "answer_id" : 43369048,
    "question_id" : 3101128,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>We face this error when permanent generation heap is full and some of us we use command prompt to build our maven project in windows. since we need to increase heap size, we could set our environment variable @ControlPanel/System and Security/System and there you click on  <strong><em>Change setting</em></strong> and select Advanced and set Environment variable as below</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Variable-name : MAVEN_OPTS</li>\n<li>Variable-value : -XX:MaxPermSize=128m</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1921531,
      "reputation" : 17338,
      "user_id" : 1732936,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 66,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f107992a766854d72c417ca7d27456aa?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Xelian",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1732936/xelian"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1498476561,
    "creation_date" : 1498476561,
    "answer_id" : 44758705,
    "question_id" : 3101128,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This very annoying error so what I did:\nUnder Windows:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Edit system environment variables - &gt; Edit Variables -&gt; New\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>then fill </p>\n\n<pre><code>MAVEN_OPTS\n-Xms512m -Xmx2048m -XX:MaxPermSize=512m\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Veajs.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Veajs.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p>Then restart the console and run the maven build again. No more Maven space/perm size problems.</p>\n"
  } ],
